                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.77 Chinese Eastern/216: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-08-18T16:00:00+08:00"
                            >August 18, 1929—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received August 19—1:25 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>730. Legation’s 729, August 18, 2 p.m. Following from American Consul at Harbin:
                        <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“August 17, 2 p.m. Reliable reports received to the effect that clashes
                            have occurred with few casualties both sides between small detachments
                            Chinese-Soviet troops near Manchuria Station and Suifenho. Heavy
                            aircraft, Soviet artillery shooting taking place near both places
                            evidently to intimidate Chinese.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">MacMurray</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
